1
00:00:02,065 --> 00:00:04,192
[♪ theme music playing]

2
00:00:27,632 --> 00:00:31,053
THE HUSBAND

3
00:00:35,307 --> 00:00:36,433
THIS SERIES IS FICTITIOUS

4
00:00:36,516 --> 00:00:39,144
CHILDREN WERE FILMED SAFELY
GEN AI WAS USED IN SELECT SCENES

5
00:00:39,645 --> 00:00:41,730
WOORI TOGETHER MEDICAL CENTER

6
00:00:41,813 --> 00:00:42,814
[Dr. Ko] Dr. Kang.

7
00:00:45,025 --> 00:00:46,151
I mean, Taeju.

8
00:00:51,114 --> 00:00:52,616
Are you really going to…

9
00:00:55,744 --> 00:00:56,870
end things with Seyun?

10
00:01:01,458 --> 00:01:03,001
I don't know… [sighs]

11
00:01:05,337 --> 00:01:07,005
…if I can do this anymore.

12
00:01:09,341 --> 00:01:10,759
[sighs]

13
00:01:11,385 --> 00:01:14,012
I think this is
where we should end it, Father.

14
00:01:14,721 --> 00:01:15,931
[Dr. Ko] Listen.

15
00:01:16,014 --> 00:01:18,016
I know how you feel.

16
00:01:19,810 --> 00:01:23,105
You see, that's just how life is.

17
00:01:24,064 --> 00:01:25,065
Taeju.

18
00:01:25,982 --> 00:01:27,651
Do you think I've never felt that way?

19
00:01:28,694 --> 00:01:29,986
I've been there.

20
00:01:30,987 --> 00:01:33,240
I wanted to give it all up and run away.

21
00:01:35,075 --> 00:01:37,119
But I had a family to protect.

22
00:01:38,662 --> 00:01:40,455
I just had to suck it up.

23
00:01:42,207 --> 00:01:44,584
That's how I kept myself going.

24
00:01:51,049 --> 00:01:52,300
[sighs]

25
00:01:59,683 --> 00:02:00,809
Your heart,

26
00:02:02,352 --> 00:02:04,146
your values, your morals…

27
00:02:06,022 --> 00:02:07,399
Just put them all aside.

28
00:02:11,361 --> 00:02:13,113
Don't let Seyun see them.

29
00:02:14,489 --> 00:02:18,994
It'd only hurt her, all right?

30
00:02:20,245 --> 00:02:22,247
[pensive music plays]

31
00:02:26,376 --> 00:02:28,211
EPISODE 5

32
00:02:47,939 --> 00:02:50,317
BEHAVIORAL HEALTH
CONSULTATION ROOM

33
00:03:13,590 --> 00:03:14,966
Come on in, Taeju.

34
00:03:23,058 --> 00:03:24,476
[music ends]

35
00:03:24,559 --> 00:03:25,560
Are you okay?

36
00:03:27,729 --> 00:03:29,397
[sighs] No.

37
00:03:33,276 --> 00:03:34,528
[sighs]

38
00:03:34,611 --> 00:03:37,239
Sounds like the talk didn't go well.

39
00:03:39,658 --> 00:03:40,742
[sighs]

40
00:03:41,952 --> 00:03:44,663
[clock ticking]

41
00:03:52,963 --> 00:03:54,881
It's okay. It happens.

42
00:04:02,264 --> 00:04:03,265
[sighs]

43
00:04:07,852 --> 00:04:09,521
It's okay, Taeju.

44
00:04:09,604 --> 00:04:12,357
[♪ slow guitar music playing]

45
00:04:14,651 --> 00:04:15,652
Don't you worry.

46
00:04:16,820 --> 00:04:18,154
This isn't the end.

47
00:04:26,538 --> 00:04:31,459
THE HUSBAND

48
00:04:33,545 --> 00:04:34,546
[music ends]
STYLE
::cue()

49
00:04:44,347 --> 00:04:45,515
Where are we?

50
00:04:48,727 --> 00:04:50,270
I thought we were going to my wife.

51
00:04:50,770 --> 00:04:53,315
That's for you
to figure out from here on out.

52
00:04:56,443 --> 00:05:00,071
It's the exact same MO
as my wife's murder six years ago.

53
00:05:00,155 --> 00:05:02,032
[♪ dramatic music plays]

54
00:05:02,115 --> 00:05:03,909
ESTIMATED TOD
36-37 HRS AFTER RANSOM CALL

55
00:05:03,992 --> 00:05:10,332
His window for murder is
36 to 38 hours post-ransom call.

56
00:05:11,291 --> 00:05:15,295
It's already been 15 hours
since he took your wife.

57
00:05:16,671 --> 00:05:18,590
Your wife is still alive.

58
00:05:19,758 --> 00:05:21,468
Though she doesn't have much time left.

59
00:05:22,052 --> 00:05:23,595
So what do I have to do now

60
00:05:24,220 --> 00:05:25,472
to save my wife?

61
00:05:26,932 --> 00:05:27,974
To pick up the money.

62
00:05:28,683 --> 00:05:30,060
What? Money?

63
00:05:30,560 --> 00:05:35,398
The three billion you have here.
I need you to hand it over to me.

64
00:05:35,482 --> 00:05:38,443
Let Seyun go first.
Then I'll give you the money.

65
00:05:38,526 --> 00:05:40,111
[sighs] No, Mother.

66
00:05:40,195 --> 00:05:42,948
Give me the money first.
That's the only way she'll live.

67
00:05:43,031 --> 00:05:44,532
What? [breathes shakily]

68
00:05:44,616 --> 00:05:45,867
You greedy bastard!

69
00:05:49,704 --> 00:05:50,747
[Seyun's mother] Just take it!

70
00:05:51,581 --> 00:05:53,291
Please, just take the money!

71
00:06:14,688 --> 00:06:16,439
You made it onto the news.

72
00:06:19,567 --> 00:06:21,111
The culprit must've seen it too.

73
00:06:23,697 --> 00:06:26,157
CHOI HYEONSU
NATIONAL POLICE AGENCY

74
00:06:27,826 --> 00:06:29,035
[Taeju] The NFS?

75
00:06:29,119 --> 00:06:31,329
You want me to go there? Why?

76
00:06:31,830 --> 00:06:33,665
[Suhyeong]
To find the bait to lure him out.

77
00:06:33,748 --> 00:06:35,709
REVEALING THE TRUTH
WITH THE POWER OF SCIENCE

78
00:06:44,551 --> 00:06:45,844
SEOUL SEONGJIN POLICE STATION

79
00:06:46,386 --> 00:06:48,722
URGENT RETRIEVAL OF THE ABOVE
FORENSIC EVIDENCE ITEMS

80
00:06:51,474 --> 00:06:55,353
Hi, I'm with Seongjin Police.
I'm here to urgently collect the evidence.

81
00:06:55,437 --> 00:06:57,230
Okay, give me a moment.

82
00:06:57,731 --> 00:06:59,733
[music continues]

83
00:07:30,513 --> 00:07:31,514
[music ends]

84
00:07:35,518 --> 00:07:38,271
[Taeju] How are we supposed to use
surveillance cameras to contact him?

85
00:07:38,354 --> 00:07:39,606
KIDNAPPING OF KO SEYUN

86
00:07:39,689 --> 00:07:41,691
[♪ tense music playing]

87
00:07:45,737 --> 00:07:48,531
LOCATION: 145-138 SONGLIM-DONG

88
00:07:48,615 --> 00:07:51,951
CAMERA POSITION AT THE TIME
OF INITIAL DISCOVERY NEAR ENTRYWAY

89
00:07:52,035 --> 00:07:54,579
[Suhyeong] The detectives found them
at your in-laws'.

90
00:08:10,720 --> 00:08:12,096
Captain!

91
00:08:12,180 --> 00:08:13,264
Over here.

92
00:08:19,646 --> 00:08:20,730
Take a look.

93
00:08:21,523 --> 00:08:22,732
[beeping]

94
00:08:25,568 --> 00:08:26,569
[agent] Detective.

95
00:08:27,737 --> 00:08:29,864
[Suhyeong]
They found cameras at your house too.

96
00:08:34,702 --> 00:08:35,829
[officer] Over here!

97
00:08:39,249 --> 00:08:42,210
[Suhyeong] And these cameras were found
during a follow-up search.

98
00:08:45,296 --> 00:08:46,631
He's been…

99
00:08:49,717 --> 00:08:51,553
watching you all along.

100
00:09:02,605 --> 00:09:06,192
[Seyun screaming]
STYLE
::cue()

101
00:09:08,444 --> 00:09:09,737
[music ends]

102
00:09:35,305 --> 00:09:38,725
[♪ dramatic music playing]

103
00:10:07,253 --> 00:10:08,504
[beeps]

104
00:10:11,799 --> 00:10:14,636
What on earth is this guy doing? Geez…

105
00:10:14,719 --> 00:10:16,596
[beeping]

106
00:10:21,476 --> 00:10:22,477
Hmm?

107
00:10:35,406 --> 00:10:36,407
[beeps]

108
00:11:09,065 --> 00:11:10,066
[music ends]

109
00:11:10,942 --> 00:11:13,361
[line ringing]

110
00:11:14,153 --> 00:11:15,989
UNKNOWN NUMBER

111
00:11:20,410 --> 00:11:21,536
[Taeju] Hello?

112
00:11:23,246 --> 00:11:24,747
It's been a while, Mr. Kang.

113
00:11:25,957 --> 00:11:28,376
I thought I'd never see you again,
but here you are.

114
00:11:29,210 --> 00:11:31,254
Can we skip the pleasantries?

115
00:11:33,339 --> 00:11:35,341
You've gotten real famous in the meantime.

116
00:11:35,425 --> 00:11:37,593
I wasn't sure
it was the same Mr. Kang I knew.

117
00:11:37,677 --> 00:11:39,679
I'm honestly surprised.

118
00:11:40,513 --> 00:11:41,764
And my wife?

119
00:11:44,642 --> 00:11:45,893
Where is she?

120
00:11:51,149 --> 00:11:52,150
She is…

121
00:11:54,986 --> 00:11:56,362
still alive, right?

122
00:11:58,948 --> 00:12:00,366
[sighs]

123
00:12:04,078 --> 00:12:05,121
For now, yes.

124
00:12:07,081 --> 00:12:08,082
[sighs]

125
00:12:10,335 --> 00:12:12,170
Just out of genuine curiosity…

126
00:12:14,547 --> 00:12:16,341
Why are you really doing this to us?
STYLE
::cue()

127
00:12:17,884 --> 00:12:20,887
You asked me for a favor, and I delivered.

128
00:12:20,970 --> 00:12:22,513
So what kind of question is that?

129
00:12:23,222 --> 00:12:25,141
What am I even supposed to say?

130
00:12:25,933 --> 00:12:28,895
No. Cut the crap already.

131
00:12:28,978 --> 00:12:31,230
Why are you really doing this to us?

132
00:12:31,856 --> 00:12:32,857
Listen, boss.

133
00:12:33,524 --> 00:12:36,027
That shouldn't even matter
to you right now.

134
00:12:36,778 --> 00:12:40,490
What should matter is
that your wife is going to die,

135
00:12:40,573 --> 00:12:44,452
and you're going to have to live
with the guilt for the rest of your life.

136
00:12:47,246 --> 00:12:49,665
[♪ suspenseful music playing]

137
00:13:12,939 --> 00:13:15,108
[sighs]

138
00:13:23,408 --> 00:13:24,742
Here's your money as promised.

139
00:13:28,579 --> 00:13:30,164
For real this time.

140
00:13:39,006 --> 00:13:41,926
Mr. Kang, it's already over.

141
00:13:42,593 --> 00:13:43,845
It's too late.

142
00:13:45,221 --> 00:13:47,265
How does Hogok Park in three hours sound?

143
00:13:50,309 --> 00:13:51,811
Did you not hear me? [sighs]

144
00:13:58,067 --> 00:13:59,193
[chuckles]

145
00:13:59,944 --> 00:14:01,028
Is this funny?

146
00:14:01,946 --> 00:14:03,489
[Taeju] Yeah, it is.

147
00:14:04,949 --> 00:14:07,451
You knew it was me
when you accessed this camera.

148
00:14:08,953 --> 00:14:10,079
Why did you even call me?

149
00:14:11,372 --> 00:14:12,999
Did you just want to hear my voice?

150
00:14:15,751 --> 00:14:17,420
You do want the money, don't you?

151
00:14:20,673 --> 00:14:22,717
Three billion won in cash.

152
00:14:24,010 --> 00:14:26,012
It's not mixed in
with 1,000-won bills either.

153
00:14:26,095 --> 00:14:27,722
This is the real deal.

154
00:14:30,224 --> 00:14:31,934
You're saying you don't want it, right?

155
00:14:55,625 --> 00:14:57,501
I might as well destroy it then.

156
00:15:02,340 --> 00:15:04,508
[Mr. Noh] Okay. Fine.

157
00:15:05,343 --> 00:15:07,720
You've gotten pretty smart, Mr. Kang.
[chuckles]

158
00:15:09,055 --> 00:15:10,306
All right.

159
00:15:11,098 --> 00:15:13,100
Why don't we talk this out?

160
00:15:13,184 --> 00:15:15,561
[Taeju] Yeah, I'd love to.

161
00:15:16,229 --> 00:15:17,230
But first,

162
00:15:18,189 --> 00:15:20,816
I need to confirm my wife is alive.

163
00:15:22,068 --> 00:15:23,569
Put her on the phone.
STYLE
::cue()

164
00:15:33,204 --> 00:15:34,205
[music ends]

165
00:16:26,424 --> 00:16:27,425
[grunts]

166
00:16:54,076 --> 00:16:56,287
-[thud]
-[gasps]

167
00:16:57,997 --> 00:16:59,999
[♪ tense music playing]

168
00:17:06,464 --> 00:17:08,799
[breathing heavily]

169
00:17:13,304 --> 00:17:14,305
Come on.

170
00:17:15,222 --> 00:17:17,266
Come on, please.

171
00:17:19,310 --> 00:17:21,187
[footsteps]

172
00:17:48,964 --> 00:17:50,883
[keys jingling]

173
00:18:20,037 --> 00:18:21,038
[music ends]

174
00:18:22,373 --> 00:18:24,041
[breathing heavily]

175
00:18:27,503 --> 00:18:28,796
[Seyun] Stay away from me.

176
00:18:31,882 --> 00:18:33,008
I said, stay away!

177
00:18:33,092 --> 00:18:34,385
[Mr. Noh] It's for you.

178
00:18:37,471 --> 00:18:39,807
I said it's for you.
You don't want to take the call?

179
00:18:41,642 --> 00:18:43,811
[groans] Not again.

180
00:18:44,520 --> 00:18:46,731
I keep forgetting I tied up your hands.

181
00:18:47,898 --> 00:18:50,443
This is your fault for trying to escape!

182
00:18:54,071 --> 00:18:56,240
Just talk like this. Okay?

183
00:18:59,410 --> 00:19:00,411
It's your husband.

184
00:19:02,997 --> 00:19:04,081
My husband?
STYLE
::cue()

185
00:19:05,124 --> 00:19:06,167
[Taeju] Hello?

186
00:19:06,751 --> 00:19:07,752
Seyun.

187
00:19:09,170 --> 00:19:10,171
Seyun?

188
00:19:10,254 --> 00:19:13,632
[sighs, breathes shakily]

189
00:19:13,716 --> 00:19:14,800
Is that really you?

190
00:19:14,884 --> 00:19:16,469
Yes, honey. It's me.

191
00:19:17,762 --> 00:19:18,763
Are you okay?

192
00:19:19,305 --> 00:19:20,556
Are you hurt anywhere?

193
00:19:21,557 --> 00:19:22,683
[sniffles]

194
00:19:25,519 --> 00:19:26,937
[Seyun] Yeah, I'm fine.

195
00:19:28,647 --> 00:19:30,691
[breathes shakily]

196
00:19:30,775 --> 00:19:32,276
Okay, thank goodness.

197
00:19:34,445 --> 00:19:35,446
Honey.

198
00:19:38,365 --> 00:19:40,075
I'm sorry. About everything.

199
00:19:41,368 --> 00:19:42,787
No, honey.

200
00:19:42,870 --> 00:19:45,956
No, really. I really am sorry.

201
00:19:46,832 --> 00:19:48,918
About so many different things.

202
00:19:49,627 --> 00:19:54,006
I've had so much
I've wanted to say to you.

203
00:19:54,757 --> 00:19:57,635
I don't know why
I've been putting it all off.

204
00:19:59,178 --> 00:20:00,971
Let's talk in person, okay?

205
00:20:01,055 --> 00:20:04,058
I'm coming for you. Just hang in there.

206
00:20:04,141 --> 00:20:05,142
Okay?

207
00:20:06,018 --> 00:20:07,102
Yeah.

208
00:20:07,978 --> 00:20:09,605
I'll be waiting for you.

209
00:20:10,231 --> 00:20:11,857
[Mr. Noh] You're testing my patience, man.

210
00:20:11,941 --> 00:20:12,942
Honey.

211
00:20:13,025 --> 00:20:14,610
[Mr. Noh] Okay, that's enough, right?

212
00:20:15,236 --> 00:20:17,696
All right, shall we
get back to our deal now?

213
00:20:19,865 --> 00:20:22,952
You know, I've been thinking about it.

214
00:20:24,620 --> 00:20:27,832
Why do you get to decide the location?
I'm the one holding the hostage.

215
00:20:29,041 --> 00:20:30,042
Okay.

216
00:20:32,127 --> 00:20:33,712
Go ahead. Pick one.

217
00:20:34,797 --> 00:20:37,883
[Mr. Noh] At 8 p.m. tonight,
wait in front of Dong Nam Sports Center.

218
00:20:38,968 --> 00:20:41,846
I'll tell you the exact location then.

219
00:20:42,805 --> 00:20:45,724
This time, make sure you bring the money.

220
00:20:45,808 --> 00:20:47,726
[phone beeps]

221
00:20:57,736 --> 00:20:59,655
[Seyun breathing heavily]

222
00:20:59,738 --> 00:21:01,031
[Mr. Noh] Is the scar any better yet?

223
00:21:01,532 --> 00:21:03,617
Hey, come on. Just stay still.

224
00:21:03,701 --> 00:21:05,661
[Seyun grunting]

225
00:21:06,245 --> 00:21:07,246
-[Mr. Noh] Come on!
-[breathing heavily]

226
00:21:10,416 --> 00:21:11,625
Looks all right.

227
00:21:11,709 --> 00:21:13,544
[breathing heavily]

228
00:21:14,086 --> 00:21:15,379
Ms. Ko.

229
00:21:16,797 --> 00:21:18,090
About Mr. Kang.

230
00:21:18,883 --> 00:21:20,217
Is he always this flaky?

231
00:21:22,386 --> 00:21:26,974
I mean, at first, he wanted you dead,
and now, he wants me to let you live.

232
00:21:27,057 --> 00:21:30,978
I don't know what he wants anymore.
It's so exhausting.

233
00:21:31,520 --> 00:21:32,771
What are you talking about?

234
00:21:34,356 --> 00:21:35,357
He wanted me dead?

235
00:21:35,441 --> 00:21:36,901
[Mr. Noh] Oh. [sighs]

236
00:21:36,984 --> 00:21:38,694
I guess you didn't know.

237
00:21:39,778 --> 00:21:41,864
Ugh, should I tell you this or not?

238
00:21:42,656 --> 00:21:44,742
[♪ dramatic music playing]

239
00:21:46,827 --> 00:21:47,953
Ms. Ko.

240
00:21:48,871 --> 00:21:50,873
Mr. Kang put me up to all this.

241
00:21:50,956 --> 00:21:51,957
[Seyun scoffs]

242
00:21:53,500 --> 00:21:54,877
Don't you lie to me.

243
00:21:58,881 --> 00:21:59,882
[Mr. Noh] I'm not.

244
00:22:00,799 --> 00:22:02,343
He'd never do something like that.

245
00:22:02,426 --> 00:22:05,596
I heard he asked for a divorce,
but you said no.

246
00:22:06,180 --> 00:22:08,849
That you didn't want to
give him anything he wanted.

247
00:22:13,354 --> 00:22:15,522
I'm sure that's what he told me.

248
00:22:17,191 --> 00:22:18,359
Did he not?

249
00:22:24,865 --> 00:22:26,867
[music continues]
STYLE
::cue()

250
00:22:44,218 --> 00:22:45,886
NAMGANG LIVESTOCK DISTRIBUTION

251
00:22:47,680 --> 00:22:48,681
[music ends]

252
00:22:53,602 --> 00:22:55,437
[Suhyeong] It's the black sedan out front.

253
00:22:57,523 --> 00:23:00,526
When he calls,
he'll tell you the exact location.

254
00:23:01,402 --> 00:23:04,571
Don't get worked up, and be cooperative.

255
00:23:05,280 --> 00:23:07,908
Until you know for sure
that your wife is safe,

256
00:23:07,992 --> 00:23:09,201
don't do anything rash.

257
00:23:09,284 --> 00:23:11,578
Don't react to him. Just wait.

258
00:23:13,455 --> 00:23:15,416
That's the only way
you can save your wife.

259
00:23:17,126 --> 00:23:18,377
I understand.

260
00:23:18,460 --> 00:23:19,712
Good.

261
00:23:24,925 --> 00:23:26,844
-[keypad beeping]
-[door opens]

262
00:23:32,016 --> 00:23:35,185
I'll be watching from a distance
just in case anything happens.

263
00:23:35,269 --> 00:23:38,814
When he takes the money and releases
your wife as per the agreement,

264
00:23:38,897 --> 00:23:40,649
leave with her immediately.

265
00:23:43,902 --> 00:23:45,279
And don't look back.

266
00:23:47,990 --> 00:23:50,659
